  "text": "Drug and alcohol use emerge as critical elements of HIV/STI risk in our studies of commercial and non-commercial sexual encounters. Risk taking enhanced by substance-use features prominently among patrons of entertainment venues who report alcohol use as a way to facilitate new sexual connections [CITATION_1] , market vendors who incorporate social drinking into their social and business networking [CITATION_2] , and subgroups of FSW who also use injection drugs [CITATION_3] .",
